parameters: \N<Hebeta>I'm home. Have you been a good girl while I was away?

\N<Hebeta>Ehehe... Don't worry. I managed to secure a job. That solves
our money problems.

\N<Hebeta>Plus, today I went around greeting people in town. Everyone
was so nice. They didn't make faces at me or look down on
me, even though I'm ugly.
\N<Hebeta>Well... I guess that's only for now, though.

\N<Hebeta>But that's okay. After all, I have you. To love someone with
all your heart and to be loved in return... If I can live a
life like that, I don't need anything else.

\N<Hebeta>I have such a beautiful wife... and soon we'll have a cute
little baby. If I asked for more, I'd probably be struck by
lightning.
\N<Hebeta>Even so, a baby for me, huh.

\N<Hebeta>It brings back memories. When I said I was leaving the army
to marry you.

\N<Hebeta>Ehehe... Everyone was so surprised. That someone like me
could get such a beautiful wife.

\N<Hebeta>But you were the captain's lover, so... we ended up running
away to this place.

\N<Hebeta>So, I'll make sure to make you extra happy to make up for
it, okay?

\N<Hebeta>Right? Right? Let's be happy together? For the sake of your
ex-husband who was transferred back to the main unit... and
for our son too?

\N<Hebeta>Well then, I'm off. There's an important discussion today
about that matter, so I might be late.

\N<Hebeta>Are you listening? I told you I'm meeting with the officer
in charge of Lyuda today, right?

\N<Hebeta>It's about possibly re-enlisting for the stability of our
family. It might be lonely for you, but that's what being
the head of the family is all about, right? Ehehe.

\N<Hebeta>Oh come on, don't make that face. I'll give you plenty of
attention when I get back.

\N<Hebeta>And... let's try for a second child as soon as the first one
is born, okay? Oh, and don't worry about money – that's part
of what today's discussion is about.

\N<Hebeta>Well then, I'm off. Aren't you going to say 'Take care,
dear'?
\N<Segi>A letter from Lyuda... His forgotten item...?

The Lyuda authorizes your re-enlistment. However, be deeply
aware that this is an exceptional measure.

Normally, Lyuda does not authorize re-enlistment. Re-
enlistment is only granted as an exception to those who have
made significant achievements during their service.

You previously made such achievements during the training
assembly at the Lakebed Ruins City Mive.

This re-enlistment is authorized based on those
achievements, and it should be deeply recognized once again.

To serve as proof, the details of your achievements are
listed below.
\N<Segi>You... during the time of the training assembly...

\N<Segi>At that time... you preemptively detected a plot to
assassinate Zuuteruka, who was the garrison commander... and
you reported it... swiftly...

\N<Segi>After the training assembly concluded... following the
inquiry... was... executed...

\N<Segi>The... target... name... ah, Aka... Dawn's Ear...
remnants...
